The following directions are only needed if you want to recreate the warped files yourself (provided here).

20180627.tif generated from running MintPy's save_gdal.py script within ../../mintpy2018_v9_NW_drew_water/inputs:

save_gdal.py ifgramStack.h5 -d coherence-20180603_20180627 -o 20180627.tif

The date doesn't necessarily matter, as we use the following to get the well-known text file.

gdalsrsinfo -o wkt 20180627.tif > target_NW_drew.wkt

This then gets used in sentinel1_reproject_to_unw.py:

python sentinel1_reproject_to_unw.py ../slist target_NW_drew.wkt 20180627.tif
